liking.label: Bill’s review of The Big Sleep

reviewBody.html: When I read the style of this book, I can't help but associate it with all the endless parodies out there, even down to the cartoons I watched as a kid. In spite of that, and the not-so-subtle misogyny throughout, this remains an engaging read, with lots of twists and turns, quotable lines, and doublecrosses. It's also set in possibly the rainiest week ever recorded in LA. I don't know how original Chandler's style…
